      • setCode

        public abstract void setCode()
        This method sets the values in the translation table from triplets to amino acid. Use the setCode(int,int,int,int) method to set each element. To initially set the translation table to match that of the standard code, use setStandardCode()

      • getNCBITranslationTableNumber

        public abstract int getNCBITranslationTableNumber()

      • getMinReplacementChanges

        public int getMinReplacementChanges(int aa1,
                                    int aa2)
        Returns the minimum number of replacement changes between two amino acids. If the minimum number of replacement changes is >3, MesquiteInteger.unassigned is returned.

      • getMinReplacementMatrix

        public int[][] getMinReplacementMatrix()
        Returns a 2-D array containing the minimum number of replacement changes between amino acids. If the minimum number of replacement changes is >3, MesquiteInteger.unassigned is entered.
